  "prompt": "How would you word \"damas\" and \"chambelanes\" for an english Quinceanera invitation?",
  "response": "For an English Quincea\u00f1era invitation, \"damas\" and \"chambelanes\" can be translated and worded as \"maids of honor\" and \"chamberlains\" or \"escorts,\" respectively. Here's how you might include them in the invitation:\n\n\"Join us for the Quincea\u00f1era of [Name], accompanied by her maids of honor and escorts.\" \n\nOr:\n\n\"[Name] requests the pleasure of your company at her Quincea\u00f1era, where she will be celebrated alongside her maids of honor and chamberlains.\"",
